	<title>Description of a Matrix</title>
	<sub.page.body>
		<block>
			<para>A matrix of numbers is a rectangular arrangement of numbers. Here are some examples:</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
						\left[
						\begin{array}{rrr}
						3 & 1 & -1 \\
						0 & 2 &  5
						\end{array}
						\right]
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>This is a matrix with <latex>2</latex> rows and <latex>3</latex> columns. So we call it a matrix of type <latex>(2,3)</latex>.</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
						\left[
						\begin{array}{rrrr}
						7 & -4 & 6 & 9 \\
						3 & 0 & 4 & 11 \\
						-3 & -1 & 6 & 9 \\
						2 & 2 & 0 & 4
						\end{array}
						\right]
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>This is a matrix with <latex>4</latex> rows and <latex>4</latex> columns. So we call it a matrix of type <latex>(4,4)</latex>.</para>
		</block>
		
		<block>
			<para>We have already used matrices to record the coefficients of a system of linear equations. For example, the matrices above are the (unaugmented) coefficient matrices of the systems of linear equations below.</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\begin{array}{ccccccc}
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}x} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}y} & - & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}z} & = & 0 \\
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}x} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}y} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$5$}{\color{red}z} & = & 0
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\begin{array}{rcccccrcc}
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$7$}{\color{red}r} & - & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$4$}{\color{red}s} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$6$}{\color{red}t} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$9$}{\color{red}u} & = & 0 \\
%
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$3$}{\color{red}r} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}s} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$4$}{\color{red}t} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$11$}{\color{red}u} & = & 0 \\
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$-3$}{\color{red}r} & - & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$1$}{\color{red}s} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$6$}{\color{red}t} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$9$}{\color{red}u} & = & 0 \\
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}r} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$2$}{\color{red}s} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$0$}{\color{red}t} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$4$}{\color{red}u} & = & 0 \\
\end{array}
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</block>
	</sub.page.body>
